The side <i>y</i> is divided into two pieces: one segment has length $$x$$ and the other has length $$y - x$$, so we have $x + (y-x) = y$. The area of the square with side <i>x</i> is $x^2$, and the combined area of the four rectangles is $y^2 - x^2$. The area of one rectangle is then \begin{align*}
\frac{y^2-x^2}{4} &= \frac{(y+x)(y-x)}{4}\\
&= \frac{y(y-x)}{4}
\end{align*} Since the length of one side of the rectangle is $$y-x$$, the other side has length \begin{align*}
\frac{y}{4}
\end{align*} The perimeter of the rectangle is $P = 2\left(y-x\right)+2\left(\frac{y}{4}\right) = \boxed{\frac{5}{2}y-\frac{4}{2}x}.$</think> <answer> $\frac{5}{2}y - \frac{4}{2}x$ </answer>

